## 5. Critical Path to Audit Readiness
List all items that must be completed before the audit can proceed, in priority order, with owners and deadlines.

## 6. Known Audit Risks
Identify areas likely to generate audit findings, with pre-emptive remediation status and management response prepared.

## 7. Audit Logistics
Auditor communication plan, document request process, interview scheduling, war room setup, and point of contact assignments.

## 8. Post-Audit Response Plan
Process for receiving, triaging, and responding to audit findings. Remediation tracking and management letter response procedures.

